definitions.text:
an interjection, Ho! Ah! Ha! It is supposed to imply surprise, fear and
                  indignation.
I allow, permit, let alone, leave.
Eber, father of Peleg and son of Shelah.
a Hebrew, particularly one who speaks Hebrew (Aramaic).
the Hebrew language, or rather: Aramaic.
in the Hebrew or Aramaic dialect
in the Hebrew, or rather, in the Aramaic dialect.
trans: I bring near; intrans: I come near, approach.
(a) I wake, arouse, (b) I raise up.
a renewal, dedication; the feast of rededication.
I bring a charge against, accuse
I bring a charge against, accuse.
I leave in the lurch, abandon (one who is in straits), desert.
I clothe myself (originally: I tie round in a knot).
an incision, a cutting, break; met: an interruption, a hindrance.
I dash to the ground, level with the ground.

Hezekiah, son of Ahaz, father of Manasseh, and king of Judah (727-686
                  [?] B.C.).
an ethnarch, tribal lord, a subordinate ruler.
pagan, heathen, gentile; a Gentile, non-Jew
pagan, heathen, gentile; subst: a Gentile, non-Jew.
in the manner of Gentiles, like the rest of the world.
a race, people, nation; the nations, heathen world, Gentiles.
a custom, habit; an institute, rite.
I am accustomed, custom, what was customary
I am accustomed, custom, what was customary.

visible form, shape, appearance, outward show, kind, species,
                  class.
a temple for (containing) an image (an idol).
(of meat), sacrificed to an image (or an idol).
worship or service of an image
a server (worshipper) of an image (an idol).
without a cause, purpose; purposelessly, in vain, for nothing.
I am peaceful, keep the peace, am at peace
I am peaceful, keep the peace, am at peace.

peace, peace of mind; invocation of peace a common Jewish farewell, in
                  the Hebraistic sense of the health (welfare) of an individual.
into, in, unto, to, upon, towards, for, among.
I lead in, bring in, introduce.
I go in, enter (originally: I shall go in).
I go in, come in, enter
I go in, come in, enter.
I call in (to my house), invite.
I journey in(to), I go in(to), enter, intervene.
I lead into, bring in, announce.

then, thereafter, next (marking a fresh stage); therefore, then,
                  furthermore.
from out, out from among, from

from out, out from among, from, suggesting from the interior
                  outwards.
each (of more than two), every one.
a centurion of the Roman army.
I throw, cast, put out, banish, bring forth, produce
I throw (cast, put) out; I banish; I bring forth, produce.
(a) a way out, escape, (b) result, issue.
a throwing out, a jettisoning of cargo to lighten a ship.
I give out, let, let out for my own advantage
I give out, let; middle: I let out for my own advantage.
I give justice over, defend, avenge, vindicate
I give justice over, defend, avenge, vindicate.

(a) a defense, avenging, vindication, vengeance, (b) full (complete)
                  punishment.

avenging, subst: an avenger (the word occurs frequently in the sense of
                  a special advocate [champion] of a city).
I persecute, expel by persecuting, drive out, vex, harass.
I put off, take off, strip off

I put off, take off, strip off, with acc. of person or garment or
                  both.
(a) there, yonder, in that place, (b) thither, there.
I seek out, seek out after, require.
I am greatly astonished, am awe-struck.
cast out, exposed (to the elements), abandoned.

an assembly, congregation, church; the Church, the whole body of
                  Christian believers.
I fall away from, turn away

(lit: I bend away from), I fall away from, turn away (from),
                  deviate.
I carry out (of the city gate for burial).
I cut out (off, away), remove, prevent.
I hang out, mid: I hang upon.
I forget entirely, make to forget.
I pick out for myself, choose, elect, select.
I fail, die out, come to an end, am defunct.

chosen out, elect, choice, select, sometimes as subst: of those chosen
                  out by God for the rendering of special service to Him (of the Hebrew race,
                  particular Hebrews, the Messiah, and the Christians).
a choosing out, selecting, choice by God
a choosing out, selecting, choice (by God).
I am unstrung, become weak, fail

I loose, release, unloose (as a bow-string), relax, enfeeble; pass: I
                  am faint, grow weary.
I deride, scoff at, mock greatly
I deride, scoff at, mock greatly.
I escape, get clear of, deviate, withdraw.
I return to soberness of mind
I return to soberness of mind.
willing, with right good will, voluntary, spontaneous.
willingly, of one's own accord, spontaneously.
I put to the test, make trial of, tempt
I put to the test, make trial of, tempt, try.
I fall out, fall off, fall away, fade away, wither away
I sail out (of harbor), sail away.
I fill completely, fulfill in every particular

I fill completely, fulfill in every particular (to the utmost), make
                  good.
I strike with panic or shock; I amaze, astonish.
(lit: I breathe out), I breathe my last, expire.

I depart from; I am voided, cast out; I proceed from, am spoken; I
                  burst forth, flow out, am spread abroad.
I spit upon, disdain, reject, loathe
I spit out, disdain, reject, loathe.
I root out, pluck up by the roots.

(properly: distraction or disturbance of mind caused by shock),
                  bewilderment, amazement; a trance.
I change for the worse, corrupt, pervert
I change for the worse, corrupt, pervert.

I stretch out (forth), cast forth (as of an anchor), lay hands
                  on.
I complete, bring to completion, carry out, perform.
intent, constant, strenuous, intense; met: earnest, zealous.
I put out or expose a child, set forth, explain

(a) I put out or expose a child, (b) mid: I set forth, expound,
                  explain.
I shake off; mid: I shake off from myself.
without, outside, except, the outside, apart from

(a) adv: (1) without, outside, beyond, (2) except, (3) subst: the
                  outside, (b) prep: outside, apart from.

(lit: I turn out from); mid. and pass: I turn aside (from the right
                  road), wander, forsake, and with an object: I remove from myself, shun,
                  avoid.
(strictly: a lifeless abortion) an untimely birth.

I bring out, carry out, sometimes out of the city for burial; I bring
                  forth, bear, produce.
I flee out, away, I escape
I flee out, away, escape; with an acc: I escape something.
I put forth, cause to sprout
I put forth, cause to sprout.
I pour out (liquid or solid); I shed, bestow liberally.
I go out, depart from, withdraw, flee.
I breathe my last, die, expire
I breathe my last, die, expire.
an olive tree; the Mount of Olives.

an Elamite, one of a people living to the north of the Persian Gulf in
                  the southern part of Persia.
(a) trans: I drive (on), propel, (b) intrans: I row.

least, smallest, but perhaps oftener in the weaker sense: very little,
                  very small.
Eleazar, son of Eliud, and father of Matthan.
a proof, possibly: a persuasion; reproof.

(a) I reprove, rebuke, discipline, (b) I expose, show to be
                  guilty.
abstr: alms-giving, charity; concr: alms, charity.
freedom, liberty, especially: a state of freedom from slavery.

Eliakim, son of Abiud and father of Azor; son of Melea and father of
                  Jonam.
Eliezer, son of Joram and father of Joshua.
Eliud, son of Achim, and father of Eleazar.
Elizabeth, mother of John the Baptizer.
I roll, roll up, fold up.
I afflict with sores; pass: I am afflicted with sores.
I drag, draw, pull, persuade, unsheathe.
Hellas, the native name for Greece.

a Hellene, the native word for a Greek; it is, however, a term wide
                  enough to include all Greek-speaking (i.e. educated) non-Jews.

a Hellenist, Grecian Jew, a Greek-speaking Jew, that is one who can
                  speak Greek only and not Hebrew (or Aramaic).
I charge to, put to one's account
I charge to, put to one's account, impute.
Elmadam, father of Cosam, son of Er.
I hope, hope for, expect, trust.
Elymas, the name of the sorcerer at Paphos.
I step in; I go onboard a ship, embark.
I enter, set foot on, intrude, pry into.
trans: I embark, put on board, step into.
I look into (upon); met: I consider; I see clearly.

I snort (with the notion of coercion springing out of displeasure,
                  anger, indignation, antagonism), express indignant displeasure with some one; I
                  charge sternly.

Emmanuel, a Messianic title derived from Isaiah 7:14 = God with
                  us.
Emmaus, a village not far from Jerusalem.
I remain or abide in, abide by, maintain
I remain (abide) in, abide by, maintain, persevere in.
Hamor, a man whose sons sold a field at Shechem to Jacob.
I walk about in a place
I walk about in a place, live among, am conversant with.
I fall in, am cast in
I fall in, am cast in, am involved in.
I enfold, entangle; pass: I am involved in.
I travel as a merchant, engage in trade

I travel as a merchant, engage in trade; I traffic in, make gain or
                  business of.
a place of traffic, mart, market, market-house.
a merchant, trader; one on a journey.
I burn, set on fire, suffer inflammation
I burn, set on fire, suffer inflammation.

in front, before the face; sometimes made a subst. by the addition of
                  the article: in front of, before the face of.
I make visible, report against, appear before

I make visible (manifest); hence: I report (inform) against; pass: I
                  appear before.
inborn, ingrown, congenital, natural, rooted, implanted.
before, in the presence of, in the eyes of
before, in the presence of, in the eyes of.
I begin (in), make a beginning, commence.
(a thing proved, hence) a plain token (sign, proof).
a showing, proof, demonstration, sign, token.
I am at home, live in a place.

(somewhat rare) (of clothing: I put on another); mid: I put on
                  (myself).
the material of a building, a structure
the material of a building, a structure.

I glorify, acknowledge the glory belonging to, recognize as glorious;
                  pass: I am glorified in.
I fill with power, strengthen, make strong.
I clothe; mid: I enter, creep into.
I lie in wait for, seek to entrap, defraud, deceive

I lie in wait (ambush) for, seek to entrap (hence: I defraud,
                  deceive).
I wrap up, roll up in something
I wrap up, roll up in (something), wind in.
for the sake of, on account of, wherefore

for the sake of, on account of, on account of which, wherefore, on
                  account of what, why.

working, action, productive work, activity; in the NT, confined to
                  superhuman activity.

I work, am operative, am at work, am made to work, accomplish; mid: I
                  work, display activity.
effective, productive of due result, at work.

(a) I have a grudge against, am angry (with), (b) pass. or mid: I am
                  entangled, entangle myself.
I meditate upon, reflect upon, ponder.
I place in or upon, am at hand, am present, threaten

I place in or upon; only in the intrans. tenses: I impend, am at hand,
                  am present, threaten; as adj: present.
I make a sign to by nodding
I make a sign to by nodding.
thinking, consideration; a thought, purpose, design, intention.

(a) legal, statutory, duly constituted, (b) under the law, obedient to
                  the law.
I dwell in, am settled in
I dwell in, am settled (stationary) in; met: I am indwelling.
I disturb, cause tumult, trouble, annoy.

involved in, held in, hence: liable, generally with dat. (or gen.) of
                  the punishment.
embalming, preparation of a body for burial
embalming, preparation of a body for burial.
hence, from this place, on this side and on that
hence, from this place, on this side and on that.

(lit: approaching the king, hence a technical term), a petition,
                  prayer, intercession.
(held precious, hence) precious, honored, honorable in rank.
belonging to the place, native, resident
belonging to the place, native, resident; subst: a citizen.
I turn to confusion, put to shame, reverence

(a) I turn to confusion, put to shame, (b) mid: I reverence,
                  regard.
I nourish on, am educated in
I nourish (sustain) on, am educated in.
I meet, encounter, call upon, make a petition

(a) I meet, encounter, hence: (b) I call (upon), make a petition, make
                  suit, supplication.
I wrap up, roll round, envelop
I wrap up, roll round, envelop.
I insult, outrage, treat contemptuously, mock at.
I dream (see visions) in my sleep.
before the face of, in the presence of
before the face of, in the presence of, in the eyes of.
Enosh (also Enos), son of Seth, and father of Cainan.
I take into my ear, listen to
I take into my ear, give ear to, listen to.
Enoch, son of Jared and father of Methuselah.

I buy out, buy away from, ransom; mid: I purchase out, buy, redeem,
                  choose.
I lead out, sometimes to death, execution.

I take out, remove; sometimes (mid): I choose, sometimes: I
                  rescue.
I demand of, ask for, beg earnestly for.
I plaster, wash over; I wipe off, wipe out, obliterate.
a rising up and out, resurrection.
I rise (spring) up out (of the ground).

(a) in trans. tenses: I raise up, cause to grow, (b) in intrans.
                  tenses: I rise up from.
I am utterly without resource, am in despair
I am utterly without resource, am in despair.
I send away, send forth (a person qualified for a task).

(a) I fit up, completely furnish, equip, furnish, supply, (b) I
                  accomplish, finish.
I flash forth like lightning, gleam, am radiant.
(originally: I shall go out), I go out (away), depart.

(lit: I draw out of the right place, or I draw aside out of the right
                  way), I entice.
I search diligently, I examine carefully (minutely).
I examine, question, inquire at, search out.
I lead, show the way; met: I unfold, narrate, declare.
next in order, the next day

next in order, the next day, the following day, at the period
                  immediately following.

I sound out (forth) (referring either to the clearness or to the
                  loudness of the sound).

condition, state, habit, use, especially: good condition of body or
                  soul.

(lit: I remove from a standing position), (a) in trans. tenses: I
                  astonish, amaze, (b) in intrans. tenses: I am astonished, amazed; I am out of my
                  mind, am mad.
I have strength for, am perfectly able
I have strength for (a difficult task), am perfectly able.

(a) an exit, going out, departure from a place; the exodus, (b)
                  death.
I destroy utterly, annihilate, exterminate, root out.

(a) I consent fully, agree out and out, (b) I confess, admit,
                  acknowledge (cf. the early Hellenistic sense of the middle: I acknowledge a debt),
                  (c) I give thanks, praise.
I adjure, put to oath; I exorcise.

an exorcist, a caster out of evil spirits by the use of names or
                  spells.
(a) I dig out, hence: I open up, (b) I gouge.
I set at naught, ignore, despise.
I set at naught, ignore, despise.

(a) power, authority, weight, especially: moral authority, influence,
                  (b) in a quasi-personal sense, derived from later Judaism, of a spiritual power,
                  and hence of an earthly power.

I exercise (wield) power (authority), pass: I am ruled, am held under
                  authority.

(a) from outside, from without, (b) outside, both as adj. and prep;
                  with article: the outside.

I drive out, expel, propel, thrust out; I drive out of the sea, drive
                  on shore.
I take part in a festival, keep a feast (allegorically).
I bring upon; met: I cause to be imputed to.
I gather together, crowd upon, press around
I gather together, pass: I crowd upon (some one), press around.
I am ashamed, am ashamed of.
I beg, am a beggar, ask alms.

I follow close after, accompany, dog; I imitate, pursue, am studious
                  of.
I listen to, hear, hearken to.

(a) nautical: I put out (from the shore), (lit: I take up a ship on to
                  the high seas), (b) I go up, possibly: I go up again, return.
I remind, possibly: I remind again.
I rest upon, rely on, trust in
I rest upon, rely on, trust in.
intrans. tenses: I rise up against.
on the top, above, superior to

(a) adv: on the top, above, (b) prep: on the top of, above, over, on,
                  above, more than, superior to.
I aid, relieve, do service, render help
I aid, relieve, do service, render help, am strong enough for.

Epaphras, Epaphroditus, a Colossian Christian, in captivity with Paul
                  in Rome.

I foam out (a metaphor from the seaweed and refuse borne on the crest
                  of waves), vomit forth.

Epaphras, Epaphroditus, a Colossian Christian, in captivity with Paul
                  in Rome.
of time: when, after; of cause: since, because; otherwise: else.

of time: when, now, after that; of cause: seeing that, forasmuch
                  as.
bringing in (besides or in addition), introduction, importation.
I have on over (as a garment); mid: I put on myself in addition.
a coat, outer wrap or tunic.
I come to, arrive, come on, come upon, attack.
inquiry, request, appeal, demand; a profession, pledge.
I hold forth, pay attention, note, delay

(a) trans: I hold forth, (b) intrans: I mark, pay attention (heed),
                  note; I delay, stay, wait.
I insult, treat wrongfully, molest, revile.
on, to, against, on the basis of, at
on, to, against, on the basis of, at.

(a) I set foot on, step on, (b) I mount (a horse), board (a
                  vessel).
I throw upon, lay, strike upon

(a) I throw upon, cast over, (b) I place upon, (c) I lay, (d) intrans:
                  I strike upon, rush.
I put a burden on, am burdensome.
I look with favor on, regard.
I cry out to or against
I cry out to or against.
I marry a deceased brother's wife
I take to wife after, marry a deceased brother's wife.

(a) on the earth, belonging to the earth (as opposed to the sky), (b)
                  in a spiritual sense, belonging to the earthly sphere, earthly (as opposed to
                  heavenly).
I arise, spring up, arrive, come on.
I come to know, discern, recognize

I come to know by directing my attention to him or it, I perceive,
                  discern, recognize; aor: I found out.

knowledge of a particular point (directed towards a particular object);
                  perception, discernment, recognition, intuition.
I write upon, inscribe, imprint a mark on.
I show, display, point out, indicate; I prove, demonstrate.
I sojourn, am resident (temporarily, in a foreign city).

I make an additional testamentary disposition, I furnish with
                  additions.
I hand in, give up, give way

(a) trans: I hand in, give up, (b) intrans: I give way (to the
                  wind).
I set in order besides, put in order, correct.
I sink, set, set during, go down.
gentle, mild, forbearing, fair, reasonable, moderate.
I seek after, desire, search for
I seek after, desire, search for, make inquiries about.
at the point of death, condemned to death
at the point of death, condemned to death.
a laying on; an attack, assault.
I long for, covet, lust after
I long for, covet, lust after, set the heart upon.
desire, eagerness for, inordinate desire, lust
desire, eagerness for, inordinate desire, lust.
I sit upon, cause to sit upon.
I call by an additional name, appeal to

(a) I call (name) by a supplementary (additional, alternative) name,
                  (b) mid: I call upon, appeal to, address.
I put a cover on, cover up.

on whom a curse has been invoked, accursed, doomed to
                  destruction.

(a) dat: I am placed upon, am laid upon, lie upon, am imposed; I press
                  upon, (b) absol: I press hard, am insistent, insist.
an Epicurean, one who holds the tenets of Epicurus.

I lay hold of, take hold of, seize (sometimes with beneficent,
                  sometimes with hostile, intent).
I call, choose for myself, am named
I call; mid: I choose for myself; pass: I am named.
remaining, that is left over, still left.
I loose, release; I solve, settle, explain, interpret, decide.
I testify earnestly, bear witness to.
I take care of, attend to
I take care of, attend to.
(a) I remain, tarry, (b) I remain in, persist in.
I nod to, assent to, consent.
I take an oath, swear falsely
I take an oath, swear falsely.
I fall upon, press upon, light upon, come over.
I rebuke, chide, reprove, strike at.
I long for, strain after, desire greatly
I long for, strain after, desire greatly, have affection for.
I look upon, visit, look out, select
I look upon, visit, look out, select.
I raise a tent over, dwell
I raise a tent (over), dwell, spread a tabernacle over.
I exercise oversight, care for, visit.

(used as an official title in civil life), overseer, supervisor, ruler,
                  especially used with reference to the supervising function exercised by an elder
                  or presbyter of a church or congregation.
(lit: I draw over), mid: I become as uncircumcised.
I write, send by letter to.
I prop up, uphold, support, confirm, make stronger.
I muzzle, silence, stop the mouth.

(a) trans: I turn (back) to (towards), (b) intrans: I turn (back) (to
                  [towards]); I come to myself.
I persist, insist, am more urgent.
I heap up, obtain a multitude of
I heap up, obtain a multitude of.
I put, place upon, lay on
I put, place upon, lay on; I add, give in addition.
(a) I rebuke, chide, admonish, (b) I warn.
I turn to, commit, entrust; I allow, yield, permit.

(a) (procurator) a steward, (b) (tutor) a guardian (appointed for an
                  "infant" [under 14 perhaps] by the father or by a magistrate).

I appear (as of a light in the heavens or from the heavens), shine
                  upon.
I shine upon, give light to
I shine upon, give light to.
I call out, shout, clamor at.
I force forward, run (a ship) aground.
I name, impose a name on
I name, impose a name on; pass: am named.
I am an eyewitness of, behold
I am an eyewitness of, behold, look upon.

heavenly, celestial, in the heavenly sphere, the sphere of spiritual
                  activities; met: divine, spiritual.
Erastus, steward of Corinth, a Christian.
I work, trade, perform, do, practice, commit, acquire by labor.

working, activity, work, service, trade, business, gains of business,
                  performance, practice.
a field-laborer; then: a laborer, workman in general.

work, task, employment; a deed, action; that which is wrought or made,
                  a work.
I stir up, arouse to anger, provoke, irritate, incite.
I stick fast, prop, fix firmly.
(lit: I belch forth, hence) I utter, declare.

(denoting speech in progress), (a) I say, speak; I mean, mention, tell,
                  (b) I call, name, especially in the pass., (c) I tell, command.
a desert place, desert, uninhabited region.

as an adj: deserted, desolate, waste; hence: the desert, to the east
                  and south of Palestine; of a person: deserted, abandoned, desolate.

(a) I make desolate, bring to desolation, destroy, waste, (b) of a
                  person: I strip, rob.

(the seeking of followers and adherents by means of gifts, the seeking
                  of followers, hence) ambition, rivalry, self-seeking; a feud, faction.
(a) I translate, explain, (b) I interpret the meaning of.

(a) Hermes, the messenger and herald of the Greek gods, or rather the
                  corresponding Lycaonian deity, (b) Hermes, a Roman Christian.
a creeping creature, reptile, especially a serpent.

(a) I ask (a question), question, (b) I request, make a request to,
                  pray.

I eat, partake of food; met: I devour, consume (e.g. as rust
                  does).
Esli, son of Naggai and father of Nahum.
a mirror, looking-glass (made of highly polished metal).
Hezron, son of Perez, father of Ram.
last, at the last, finally, till the end.

extremely, utterly; to be at the extremity, to be "in extremis," to be
                  at the last grasp.

within, inside, with verbs either of rest or of motion; prep: within,
                  to within, inside.

(a) from within, from inside, (b) within, inside; with the article: the
                  inner part, the inner element, (c) the mind, soul.
inner; with the article: the part that is within.

speaking another language; subst: one who speaks another
                  language.

I teach different things, that is, different from the true or necessary
                  teaching.
I am yoked with one different from myself
I am yoked with one different from myself, unequally yoked.

(a) of two: another, a second, (b) other, different, (c) one's
                  neighbor.

(a) of time: still, yet, even now, (b) of degree: even, further, more,
                  in addition.
well, well done, good, rightly; also used as an exclamation.
Eve, the first woman; wife of first man Adam.
I bring good news, preach good tidings

I bring good news, preach good tidings, with or without an object,
                  expressing either the persons who receive the good news or the good news itself
                  (the good news being sometimes expressed as a person).

the good news of the coming of the Messiah, the gospel; the gen. after
                  it expresses sometimes the giver (God), sometimes the subject (the Messiah, etc.),
                  sometimes the human transmitter (an apostle).
an evangelist, bearer of good tidings
an evangelist, a missionary, bearer of good tidings.

I give pleasure to, please (perhaps with the added idea of: rendering
                  good service to).
Eubulus, a Christian with Paul in Rome.
(a) of noble birth, of high birth, (b) noble in nature.
I am well-pleased, think it good, am resolved.

(a) good-will (good-pleasure), favor, feeling of complacency of God to
                  man, (b) good-pleasure, satisfaction, happiness, delight of men.
good action, well-doing, benefiting, kind service.
I do good deeds, perform kind service, benefit.
I keep up spirit, am cheerful, am of good courage.

(a) I make straight (of the direction, not the surface, of a road), (b)
                  I guide, steer.

adj: (a) straight of direction, as opposed to crooked, (b) upright;
                  adv: immediately.
I have a good opportunity, have leisure

I have a good (favorable) opportunity, have leisure; I devote my
                  leisure to.

opportune, timely, suitable; perhaps sometimes: holiday,
                  festival.
I fear, am anxious, am cautious; I reverence.

(lit: handling well, hence) cautious, circumspect; hence: God-fearing,
                  pious.
(lit: I speak well of) I bless; pass: I am blessed.

(used only of God), blessed (as entitled to receive blessing from man),
                  worthy of praise.
willingly sharing, ready to impart, generous.
I make into a eunuch, emasculate, castrate.
a eunuch, keeper of the bed-chamber

(a) a chamberlain, keeper of the bed-chamber of an eastern potentate,
                  eunuch, (b) a eunuch, castrated person, or one who voluntarily abstains from
